    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-02T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-02T16:00:00-05:00" n="316"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/308: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-02T23:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1922—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 3—4:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>158. I received a call today from members of the revolutionary committee
                    tendering the thanks of the authorities for help given the refugees by American
                    relief organizations.<note n="5" xml:id="d316fn5">See “American Relief
                        Activities on Behalf of Greeks Evacuated from Turkish Territory,” <ref
                            target="#pg_414">pp. 414</ref> ff.</note> They referred also to <pb
                        facs="0526" n="412" xml:id="pg_412"/> arrest and trial of political
                    prisoners, and solicited my opinion. In reply I explained that an unfortunate
                    impression would be created in the United States if they proceeded to arbitrary
                    measures. I was then given assurance that an order would be issued for release
                    of all political prisoners not actually implicated in disaster in Asia Minor,
                    and that measures would be taken to insure a fair trial for those charged with
                    misconduct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
